  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "Adding more than one WordPress site to GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan involves several steps. Here is a detailed guide to help you through the process:\n\n### Step 1: Access Your GoDaddy Account\n1. Log in to your GoDaddy account.\n2. Navigate to your \"My Products\" page.\n\n### Step 2: Access Your Hosting Account\n1. Find your Deluxe hosting plan under the \"Web Hosting\" section.\n2. Click on \"Manage\" next to your Deluxe hosting plan to open your hosting dashboard.\n\n### Step 3: Add a New Domain\n1. In your hosting dashboard, look for the \"Domains\" section.\n2. Click on \"Add Domain\" or \"Add-On Domains\" (the terminology might vary).\n3. Enter the domain name you want to add. Make sure it\u2019s pointed to the GoDaddy nameservers if it\u2019s registered outside GoDaddy.\n4. Assign the directory where the files for the new WordPress site will be stored. This is typically a new folder within the \"public_html\" directory.\n\n### Step 4: Install WordPress\n1. Go back to your hosting dashboard and find the \"Installatron\" or \"One-Click Install\" feature.\n2. Select WordPress from the list of available applications.\n3. Choose the domain you just added from the dropdown menu.\n4. Follow the installation prompts, such as setting up your admin username, password, site title, and other settings.\n5. Ensure the installation directory matches the one you specified earlier.\n\n### Step 5: Configure Your New WordPress Site\n1. After installation, you can access the new WordPress site by navigating to the domain you added.\n2. Log in using the admin credentials you set during installation.\n3. Customize your site by installing themes, plugins, and configuring settings as needed.\n\n### Step 6: Repeat for Additional Sites\nIf you wish to add more WordPress sites, repeat steps 3 to 5 for each new domain.\n\n### Tips for Managing Multiple WordPress Sites\n- **File Organization**: Keep each site in its own subdirectory within the `public_html` directory for easier management.\n- **Database Management**: Each WordPress site will need its own unique database. Ensure each new installation creates a new database or manually create one through your hosting control panel.\n- **Backup**: Regularly back up each site to avoid data loss. GoDaddy often offers backup solutions, or you can use WordPress plugins for this purpose.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully add and manage multiple WordPress sites on GoDaddy\u2019s Deluxe hosting plan.",
